Got you.

00:24:39.580 --> 00:24:40.850
Done.

00:24:40.850 --> 00:24:41.680
We'd like a new color.

00:24:41.680 --> 00:24:42.310
Fine.

00:24:42.310 --> 00:24:43.000
Done.

00:24:43.000 --> 00:24:46.940
And what that means is that
now these customers have a

00:24:46.940 --> 00:24:48.490
little bit of themselves
in the product.

00:24:48.490 --> 00:24:51.870
They're not just buyers,
they're backers.

00:24:51.870 --> 00:24:53.110
They are participants.

00:24:53.110 --> 00:24:55.950
They are co-creators of
something that's not just a

00:24:55.950 --> 00:24:57.990
watch, it's a movement.

00:24:57.990 --> 00:24:59.410
It's something they
believe in.

00:24:59.410 --> 00:25:02.830
And they become evangelists
and then marketers.

00:25:02.830 --> 00:25:05.510
It's not just the moment of
backing, when you Tweet that I

00:25:05.510 --> 00:25:09.050
just backed whatsoever on
Kickstarter, but also, because

00:25:09.050 --> 00:25:11.930
they not only have bought into
this and made a bet on

00:25:11.930 --> 00:25:14.750
something before it exists, but
also contributed, many of

00:25:14.750 --> 00:25:18.650
them, to its essence, they
really want this to succeed.

00:25:18.650 --> 00:25:20.000
And they will promote
it in a way that no

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:21.400
regular customer would.

00:25:21.400 --> 00:25:25.110
So it's a simple thing,
Kickstarter, pre-orders,

00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:27.260
threshold, comments.

00:25:27.260 --> 00:25:30.740
And what is created is a crowd
funding model that is

00:25:30.740 --> 00:25:32.860
perfectly suited for the
industrialization

00:25:32.860 --> 00:25:36.090
of the Maker Movement.

